title: Roger Whittaker, whistling balladeer who found global fame, dies at 87
description: The British singer-songwriter was known for his wistful blend of folk and pop, including on the songs “Durham Town” and “The Last Farewell.”

title: Libyan officials limit media and aid groups in Derna
description: Journalists and aid groups objected Tuesday to official demands that they stay back, amid a sense of confusion over what degree of access would be permitted.

title: The Nagorno-Karabakh conflict between Armenia and Azerbaijan, explained
description: Fierce fighting between Armenia and Azerbaijan erupted in the village of Sotk near Nagorno-Karabakh, raising fears of a wider conflict.

title: Homeland Security outlines plan to stop fentanyl, precursor chemicals
description: The Department of Homeland Security released what it called a strategy for combating illicit opiods, which includes keeping fentanyl off the streets

title: U.S. touts commitment to Ukraine despite battlefield challenges
description: In the latest show of evolving military aid to Ukraine, American M1A1 Abrams tanks will soon arrive on the battlefield, officials said.

title: As Zelensky arrives at U.N. to pitch for support, Russian drones hit Lviv
description: The Ukrainian president traveled to New York to address the U.N. General Assembly and make a personal plea for support against Russian forces occupying roughly one-fifth of his country.

title: Fighting flares between Azerbaijan and Armenia in Nagorno-Karabakh
description: Azerbaijan says it launched an “anti-terrorist” campaign in the contested Nagorno-Karabakh region under Armenian control, as mortar fire and air-raid sirens are heard.

title: Biden to meet Netanyahu in N.Y., but denies him long-sought White House visit
description: President Biden will meet Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu at the U.N. General Assembly Wednesday, but there is still no coveted White House invite on the horizon.

title: Ecuador locked up a drug lord. He just released a music video from prison.
description: “El Corrido del León” — “The Lion’s Ballad” — taunts a government that has proved incapable of taking control of its prisons back from increasingly powerful gangs.

title: Who was Hardeep Singh Nijjar, the Sikh activist killed in Canada?
description: Canada has alleged that the Indian government was involved in the fatal shooting of the prominent Sikh leader, who supported an independent homeland in Punjab.

title: How to match Bukele’s success against gangs? First, dismantle democracy.
description: The Salvadoran president’s crackdown on criminal violence has made him Latin America’s most popular leader. Under a state of emergency declaration, the government is now holding 71,000 people — many, activists say, on specious grounds.

title: India, Canada expel diplomats over accusations Delhi killed Sikh activist
description: The assassination accusation of Hardeep Singh Nijjar sent relations between the two nations plummeting and holds ramifications for the U.S.-led alliance to confront China.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky and Biden to address U.N. General Assembly
description: Zelensky’s first stop during his U.S. trip was to wounded Ukrainian troops receiving medical treatment in New York.

title: At Japan’s dementia cafes, forgotten orders are all part of the service
description: As the world’s oldest society, Japan faces a pressing national health challenge in dementia. The country is trying innovative ways to keep sufferers active.

title: The main storylines at a gloomy United Nations
description: As in recent years, the U.N. General Assembly deliberations are taking place amid a profound global gloom.
